  <entry>
    <id>tag:github.com,2008:Grit::Commit/3f98190bb702ee993c01ca26bd14f360fbb5b022</id>
    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/shurik179/TQFTbook/commit/3f98190bb702ee993c01ca26bd14f360fbb5b022"/>
    <title>
        Vendor plastex + gerby-website forks; document them in README
    </title>
    <updated>2026-06-17T14:16:36Z</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/12883611?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>shurik179</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/shurik179</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;pre style=&#39;white-space:pre-wrap;width:81ex&#39;&gt;Vendor plastex + gerby-website forks; document them in README

The two forks under website/repos/ each had their own .git, so the outer
repo recorded them as empty embedded repos (nothing pushed to GitHub).
Removed the nested .git dirs so their files are tracked normally, and added
a README section with their upstream URLs + exact fork commits and where our
patches live.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 &amp;lt;noreply@anthropic.com&amp;gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
